<title>CHINA: Shanghai newspaper calls for private banks.</title>
<headline>Shanghai newspaper calls for private banks.</headline>
<dateline>SHANGHAI 1996-10-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The official Business Newspaper called on Monday for the development of private banks and financial institutions to help China's private economy grow faster.</p>
<p>China's fast-developing private firms still have difficulty getting loans from the state-owned banks which dominate the banking industry, the newspaper quoted an economist as saying.</p>
<p>There are currently no private banks in China, although there are many small-scale private credit associations which have the right to take in deposits and make loans on a limited scale.</p>
